Drain and cook for 30 minutes, turning. Cook potatoes 45 minutes and squash and eggplant for 20 minutes on coals that have burned 45 minutes.

title: pina colada muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Makes 24 muffins.

title: dutch baby pancakes
directions: You will need casserole dish, 2-quart size.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with food coloring and cocoa and add mixture.

Add salt and flour together. Add to creamed mixture, adding buttermilk a little at a time, alternately with soda and vinegar (do not beat hard), just blend. Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 2 (8-inch) round pans, greased and floured.

title: apricot-pineapple molded salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and let set until slightly thickened.
Add crushed pineapple.
Beat together cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Fold Cool Whip mixture into the Jell-O.
Pour into a shallow baking dish (8 or 9-inch square pan).
Let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: 15 minute linguine with clam sauce
directions: While pasta cooks, saute butter, onions and garlic.
Add juice from clams and milk.
Bring to boil and add thickener and clams. Before removing from heat, stir in parsley and remove; pour over pasta.
Sprinkle with "Italian cheese".
Serve with a salad and bread.

title: great gerts
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Add seasonings, flour and Rice Krispies.
Pinch off small bits with your fingers and press flat with a fork dipped in cold water.
The smaller these are the better they are.
Bake on a cookie sheet for about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: glorified (heavenly) rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill very thoroughly before serving. Serves 6 to 8.
If you choose to use Cool Whip, add just before serving instead of whipping cream.

title: chocolate oatmeal drops
directions: Put the sugar, milk and butter in boiler; boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add the cocoa, quick oats and nuts.
Stir and mix in the vanilla and pinch of salt.
Spoon out by drops on dish sprayed with Pam or greased with butter.

title: squash cookies
directions: Combine squash, sugar, oil and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to squash mixture.
Add soda, dissolved in milk.
Add vanilla.
Drop on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 375° oven.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a well-greased pan. Bake one hour or until brown at 400°.

title: oven stew
directions: Cut stew meat into small pieces.
Salt, pepper and roll in flour.
Brown in skillet.
Put stew meat, carrots, tomato sauce and cabbage in a long pan or Dutch oven.
Cover and bake 2 to 3 hours or until tender-done at 300° to 350°.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Combine spaghetti, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Place half of mixture in greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Add half of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with remaining spaghetti and Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with spaghetti sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: diabetic orange cookies
directions: Cream first three ingredients, then add the rest of the ingredients and form into 1-inch balls.
Chill.
Press a pecan half in the center.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: frozen coleslaw
directions: Combine vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 1 hour. Drain, if water accumulates.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture. Stir well. Freeze in plastic bags or container. To serve, thaw in refrigerator.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Prepare eggs and cream in blender.
Put ham and Swiss cheese in pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over it.
Cook 45 minutes at 400°.

title: frozen strawberry yummy
directions: Cut first 3 ingredients as for a crust.
Add nuts.
Spread out crumbs onto cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spread a little more than half of the crumbs into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: "jack's" crock-pot beans
directions: *Read Jack and the Bean Stalk.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In mixing bowl, add meat, rice, garlic powder, chopped onion and 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Mix all together.
Set aside.
Cut tops off green peppers and hollow.
Boil all peppers for 5 minutes, then fill each pepper with meat mixture in round, deep dish.
Pour over leftover tomato sauce.
Cook at 400° for 45 minutes.
Pour juice over if desired.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Cut in margarine.
Add milk to make a soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured board for 2 minutes.
Shape into a round loaf.
Place on greased cookie sheet, cut an `X' across the top.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients; form into balls.
Brown.
Add sauce. Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: *Or whatever vegetables you want.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Place all ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix well. Shape into loaf and cover top of loaf generously with catsup. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Can be baked on broiler pan rack so grease will not be absorbed into loaf.
Makes 10 servings.

title: german chocolate cake mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Blend well.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chinese vegetable salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Will keep for days.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Slice sweet potatoes.
Cover an iron frying pan with just enough oil to cover bottom.
Fry 1 layer of sweet potatoes at a time, turning to brown both sides, lightly.
Lift onto platter and, if desired, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar, or eat plain.

title: 4 to 6 pound brisket(freezes well)
directions: Trim all fat from brisket.
Generously cover both sides of brisket with garlic salt, celery salt and onion salt. Pour all of hickory liquid smoke; place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: peppered steak
directions: Flour, salt and pepper steak.
Brown in frying pan in oil. Place bell pepper and onion over steak.
Pour bouillon over steak and simmer for 1 hour.

title: lasagne(lite cooking)
directions: Cook and stir onions and garlic in Crisco until tender.
Add ground beef and drain if necessary.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste, basil, oregano, sugar and pepper.
Stir until well blended. Simmer 30 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and parsley; set aside.
Cook noodles 7 minutes in unsalted boiling water.
Drain.
Heat oven to 350°.
Layer all ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Bake 45 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: lipton pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into thin strips, 2-inches long.
In a large skillet, heat shortening and brown meat trimmings.
Stir in onion soup mix and *2 cups water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes (until meat is tender).
Stir in peppers and simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with 1/2 cup water.
Stir into skillet mixture. Cook until thickened.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Butter & flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, & salt.
In a cup stir milk & vanilla.
In a large bowl mix butter and sugar until yellow and fluffy.
Add 2 eggs and beat well.
Repeat and add last 2 eggs. Beat well.
With a wooden spoon stir in flour mixture.
Add milk mixture.
Spoon into pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool cake in pan 10 minutes.
Turn onto cake plate and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: goop
directions: Mix and shake.
Put in covered container.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonful into hot skillet.
Fry until crisp.

title: stuffed cabbages
directions: Core and steam cabbage until leaves can be peeled off in whole pieces.
In a large bowl, mix together meats, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Add water to meat/rice mixture until "sloppy" to the touch; more is better than not enough.
Line bottom of roast pan with outer, torn cabbage leaves (reserve enough to cover casserole, also).
Pour 1/2 can of sauerkraut over leaves.
Roll small amount of meat/rice mixture in individual cabbage leaves, starting from stem side and tucking in edges.
Place rolls in layers on top of sauerkruat.
Add remaining sauerkraut with juice, tomatoes
with juice and 1/2 can water.
Top with remaining torn leaves which will burn while cooking and will be discarded. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with mashed potatoes and crusty bread.

title: cranberry grape ice cream soda
directions: In a blender container, process grape cranberry drink and 1 scoop ice cream until smooth.
Pour into glass with remaining ice cream.
Top with soda.
Makes 1 serving.

title: vegetable soup(heart smart)
directions: In medium saucepan over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook onion and garlic about 3 minutes or until soft, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes in juice, chicken broth, carrots, celery, parsley, basil, salt and pepper and bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Add lima beans and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer about 20 minutes or until beans are tender.
Makes 6 servings, about 3/4 cup each.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Melt first two ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and mix together. Drop by teaspoonful on waffle iron and cook 1 minute. Frosting is enough for a double recipe of cookies.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; batter will be thick.
Spread into lightly greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: healthy banana-nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (200°C).
Mix both flours with sugar and walnuts.
Stir in baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Place mashed bananas in separate bowl.
Add eggs, milk and oil and mix well. Add wet ingredients to dry, mixing just until moistened.
Spoon into lightly greased muffin tins and bake 15 to 20 minutes, depending on size.
Cool on wire racks.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Grease tube pan and dust with flour.
Combine margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Fold in walnuts and halved maraschino cherries.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from pan after 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix together jello and sugar.
Add hot water.
Mix together thoroughly until jello and sugar are totally dissolved.
Add ReaLemon juice and pineapple juice; mix well.

title: twice-baked sweet potatoes
directions: Pierce potatoes with a fork. Bake at 375° for 40 to 60 minutes or until tender. Allow potatoes to cool to the touch. Cut them in half lengthwise; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell. Place pulp in a large bowl. Add orange juice. Melt 3 tablespoons butter; add to pulp and beat until smooth. Stuff the potato shells; place in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole or 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cover and cook at 350° until macaroni is tender, 55 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine and let set a couple of days before serving.

title: strawberry square salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and water together.
Add pineapple juice. Place in the refrigerator until partially congealed.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in refrigerator overnight to congeal.
Serves 24.

title: loaf pound cake
directions: In one bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Blend in butter, vanilla, egg yolks and milk.
Beat vigorously for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into a greased 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Yields one 9-inch cake.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Mix together flour, soda, cinnamon, sugar, cloves, salt and nuts and set aside.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Thaw and squeeze out spinach.
Mix with other ingredients. Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (for
a 7 x 11-inch dish).
I use a 9 x 13-inch dish and bake a little less time.

title: candied or stewed apples
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in large saucepan.
Prepare apples by cutting in half and removing cores.
Place in saucepan and sprinkle with spices and butter.
Cover and cook slowly and turn apples when about half done.
Cook until juice begins to get syrupy.

title: salisbury meatballs
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Cover with sauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh salsa
directions: In a large frying pan, cook all the chiles until black on each side, then cut chiles down the middle and remove all the seeds. Dice chiles real small.
Put into a large saucepan.
Chop onions and tomatoes real small.
Put into pan with chiles.
Add the Pace salsa to other ingredients in pan.
Also, add tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and 1 cup of water.
Let simmer for about 1 hour.
Make sure to add about 1 tablespoon of garlic salt.
Make sure to mix all ingredients well before simmering.
Makes about 6 pounds of salsa.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Cook and debone fryer.
Cut up chicken and place in a large baking dish.
Mix soup and broth; heat until creamy.
Add salt and pepper; pour over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and melted margarine. Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 450° until brown and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Cut lettuce into bite size pieces and place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Mix celery, onion, pepper, carrots and water chestnuts together; spread evenly over lettuce.
Spread Hellmann's mayonnaise over top of mixture.
Make sure you use sufficient mayonnaise, because this will become your dressing when served. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons sugar over mayonnaise.
Cover with plastic wrap; let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: curried baked fruit(prepare the day before)
directions: Drain all fruit.
Add sugar and curry to melted butter. Arrange fruit and nuts in layers in casserole; pour butter mixture over all and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Refrigerate overnight. Reheat at 350° before serving.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla. Put 1 vanilla wafer in each cupcake liner. Put 2 tablespoons of cream cheese mixture on top of vanilla wafer. Bake at 370° for 15 to 20 minutes. Let cool. Put 1 tablespoon of pie filling on top of each one.

title: possum stew
directions: Paw 'n the chillun' allus worked so hard a' catchin' little fish outta the creek that they just had to be cooked! ... but they iz sweet 'n gud eatin'.
Scales, take insides out'n the haid off ... clean in cold watah ... salt 'n roll in 1/2 meal 'n 1/2 flour ... drop in hot fat 'n brown on both sides.

To eat small bream ... furst pull fins off ... then start at the tail 'n ease meat up with a fork along backbone all the way up to whair the haid wuz ... hit'll cum off in one piece widout bones iffn you're careful.

title: broccoli-chicken-stuffing hot dish
directions: Brown chicken in margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put veggies in 2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave about 8 minutes, covered, turning once and stirring.
Put about 1/2 package of stuffing mix on top of veggies.
Mix soups and milk and pour 3/4 over stuffing.
Add chicken and pour rest of soup over chicken. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.

title: imperial crab
directions: Combine ingredients. Toss lightly.
Put in crab shells.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Put pineapple and juice in a large bowl; add pudding and mix well.
Stir in marshmallows and fold in Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 10 servings with 1 gram of fat per serving.

title: sour cream lasagne
directions: Lightly brown beef and remove excess fat.
Add tomato sauce, onions, salts and sugar.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cream together sour cream and cream cheese.
Line lightly oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish with layer of cooked noodles.
Add 1/2 of tomato mixture.
Put cream cheese mixture on top and spread evenly into layer.
Put another layer of noodles and top these with other half of tomato mixture.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: coffee-toffee torte
directions: Freeze, then crush Heath bars.
Prepare angel food cake as directed on box.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan.
Invert and cool. In saucepan, mix pudding and instant coffee, but using only 1 1/3 cups of milk for each package of pudding for a total of 2 2/3 cups of milk.
Cook according to directions on box.
Cool.
When cool, beat until mixture is smooth.
Fold in half of the whipped cream. Split cake into 3 layers.
Spread half of the pudding-cream mixture between layers.
Fold remaining whipped cream into pudding mixture and frost tops and sides of cake.
Sprinkle top and sides of cake with crushed Heath bars.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: *baklava("pita dulci")
directions: Butter a 12 x 17 x 1-inch baking pan. Butter 8 to 10 sheets of phyllo for bottom crust.
Sprinkle nuts (combined with sugar and cinnamon).
Sprinkle nuts on every sheet or every two sheets. Top with 8 sheets. Refrigerate.
Cut into diamonds. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. (After 40 minutes, lower oven to 325° for remaining 20 minutes.)
Pour cooled syrup over hot Baklava.

title: phillip's dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump pineapple into pan; spread evenly.
Dump cherry filling.
Spread evenly.
(Layer) dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer; spread evenly.
Sprinkle nuts on top of dry cake mix.
Put margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes.
Serve warm or cold. Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with juice of pineapple, Cool Whip and pudding.
Blend in pineapple, nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Put chili and peppers in crock-pot.
Add hamburger and onion, then add 1/2 box of cheese. Cook 1/2 hour.
Stir, then add remaining cheese.
Cook 1 to 2 hours in crock-pot.
Enjoy!

title: apple pie delight(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a mixing bowl combine Equal Measure, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.	Add dry mixture to apples; toss gently to coat fruit.	Fill a pastry lined 9-inch pie plate with apple mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust, that has slits in it.
Seal and flute edge.	Bake 15 minutes at 425° and turn oven down to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: roasted pecan halves
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Spread pecans on large baking sheet. Melt butter and pour over pecan halves.
Sprinkle with salt and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: orange nut glazed raisin bread
directions: Scald milk, pour over salt, sugar and butter.
Blend and cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on warm water, stir to dissolve.
Add to milk mixture with 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer, then beat in eggs, orange peel, ginger, raisins and 1/2 cup flour.
Then mix in enough remaining flour, a little at a time with spoon.
Then use hands knead until smooth into a ball. Grease and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Punch down.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Make into 2 loaves.
Make 3 slashes in top.
Let raise not more than double.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cover with sheet of foil after 20 minutes if it browns too fast.
Remove loaves from pan.
Place on wire rack, spread Orange Glaze over them, then cool.

title: fancy green beans
directions: Chop bacon in pieces,
fry in skillet.	Saute onion and pimiento in bacon grease;
add
the green beans, juice and all to mixture.
Add garlic
salt	and
Nature's
Season to taste. Simmer.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz and hominy in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Stir well; then top with crumbled corn chips.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: mustard and vinegar pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients; make sure cucumbers are covered.
Use a large container.
Let set for 3 to 4 weeks.

title: ham rolls
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave. Chop green onions and mix with cream cheese. Spread a layer over each slice of ham. Roll the ham up and slice into small sections. Place a toothpick in each one and refrigerate at least 2 hours until ready to eat.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Steam broccoli for 5 minutes (until bright green and still crisp).
Cool and chop into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add onions, olives, Miracle Whip and dill seed.
Refrigerate overnight (or for at least 8 hours); just before serving, add eggs or cheese and salt to taste.
Stir well.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: never fail caramel icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk and bring to a boil again, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Gradually add powdered sugar until thick enough to spread.

title: wild turkey salsa and rice
directions: Cut up turkey in chunks and cook in a crock-pot with water on low for 4 hours or until tender.
Saute oleo, garlic, onion and green peppers in a Dutch oven.
Add all vegetables in a Dutch oven on top of stove and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cooked turkey and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: sweet sour pork chops
directions: Brown chops in shortening; drain excess fat.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Combine ketchup and remaining ingredients; pour over chops.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes, basting occasionally, or until meat is tender.
Skim off any fat from sauce.
Makes 6 servings (1 cup sauce).

title: pink flamingo
directions: Soften cream cheese; beat until fluffy.
Add milk, lemon juice, vanilla and red food coloring.
Mix well.
Pour into a vanilla wafer crust in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Slice bananas over the top.
Spread whipped cream over the top.
Chill and serve.

title: curry-glazed chicken
directions: Place margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and heat in a 375° oven until melted.
Stir in honey, mustard and curry powder. Add chicken, turning to coat.
Bake, turning chicken over after 20 minutes.
Bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings. Contains 255 calories per serving.

title: cherry flip
directions: Mix together crackers and oleo and pat into a small oblong dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Spread on top of cooled crust.
Sprinkle nuts on cream cheese mixture.
Spread Cool Whip atop nuts.
Then spread pie filling atop the Cool Whip.
Very good!

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Start cooking on high. Turn to low and simmer 24 hours.
If too juicy, uncover last two hours of cooking time.
Your house will smell delightful!
Yields 2 to 3 pints.

title: orchard pops
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients; blend until smooth.
Pour about 1/3 cup into each of six 3-ounce paper cups.
Cover with foil.
Insert wooden stick through foil.
Freeze
for 5 hours or until firm.
Before serving, let pops stand 10 minutes at room temperature.
Remove foil and peel off paper cups.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cukes, slice or grate, also the onion.
Sprinkle with salt and set aside for 1 hour.
Squeeze a few at a time (discarding liquid).
Pour the vinegar, water, sugar, black pepper and green pepper and mix thoroughly. Add enough sour cream to make it a bit soupy. Sprinkle paprika on top before serving.

title: old-fashioned raisin bars
directions: Combine raisins and water in saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in salad dressing. Cool to lukewarm. Stir in sugar and egg. Add dry ingredients and beat.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add sugar and stir to mix thoroughly.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and add all at once, the oil, eggs and water and pumpkin.
Mix well and add nuts.
Pour batter into 3 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans.
Fill only half full.
Bake for 1 hour or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.
One loaf equals 16 slices; each slice contains 85 calories.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef.
Remove beef and drain fat. In the same skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion and pepper until tender.
Add beef, Worcestershire sauce, noodles and soups; mix well.
Spoon into a greased 3-quart casserole; top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Let stand in ice water while making roux.

title: lena's 5 pound fudge
directions: Cook together until a firm ball.
Beat until you can't beat anymore.

title: baked chicken
directions: Pour into
a
plastic bag; add 2 or 3 pieces of chicken at a time, shaking until well coated.
Melt 1 stick of margarine.
Turn over
to coat both sides.	Place in single layer. Bake at	400° for
minutes.
Turn and bake until finished browning, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: campfire bean dinner
directions: In large skillet, brown meat well.
Stir in soup mix, beans, chili sauce and water.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes.
Add cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and butter.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Refrigerate or bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 cups.

title: old fashioned light bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 3 cups flour and yeast.

In saucepan, heat milk, shortening, sugar and salt just until warm and shortening is almost melted; stir constantly. Add to flour mixture. Beat at low speed 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl. Beat 3 minutes at high speed. Gradually stir in as much flour as you can mix with a spoon.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface. Knead in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough that is smooth and elastic. Shape into a ball.
Place in a lightly greased bowl at least twice as
large as the ball of dough.
Turn dough over once to grease surface. Cover with slightly damp cloth. Allow to rise in warm place until double in size (about 1 hour).

title: merk's coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs, singly, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with sour cream, blending after each addition.
Spread half of batter in 10-inch tube pan, that has been greased and lined on the bottom with waxed paper.
Cream butter, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Add nuts; mix well.
Dot batter in pan evenly with half of nut mixture.
Cover with remaining batter. Dot with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350°, about 50 minutes.
Cool cake for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: texas meatballs and rice
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, chili powder, salt and pepper; shape into 1 1/2 to 2-inch balls.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High (100%) until meatballs are set and lose pink color, 4 to 7 minutes, rearranging meatballs after half the cooking time.
Drain. Stir in remaining ingredients; cover.
Microwave at High (100%) until mixture is bubbly and onion is tender, 4 to 7 minutes.
If using an oven without a carousel, stir after half the cooking time. Let stand until rice is tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: paul newman chicken
directions: Clean chicken and marinate several hours in dressing.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Put bread crumbs in plastic bag and shake chicken generously in crumbs.
Spray a 13 x 9 pan with Pam.
Place chicken in pan.
Cook for 1 hour, uncovered, turning once.
If chicken appears to be cooking too fast, turn oven down to 350° for the last 15 or 20 minutes.
This dish is great hot or cold.

title: spicy fruited chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil in skillet; pour off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until done, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together except pickling spice.
Pour pickling spice in a strainer and put in mixture.
Cook on low heat for 3 hours.
Remove strainer and discard spices.
Refrigerate sauce.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir over low heat until blended.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Be careful not to mistake air bubbles for boiling.
Boil slowly, stirring constantly for 5 minutes (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Stir in chips and vanilla until chips have melted.
Turn into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together
dry ingredients; set aside.
Beat butter or margarine and sugar
until	light
and
fluffy;
add
eggs. Beat well.
Stir in
milk
and
vanilla.
Add flour; mix well. Stir in nuts, dates and chopped cherries.
Shape tablespoon of dough into ball and
roll
in	Corn
Flakes.
Place on greased cookie sheet and put a quartered cherry in the middle of each. Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add pepper and ringed onions.
Mix in chili powder, tomatoes and rice.
Bake in covered dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together; add peanut butter and milk and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham crust. Freeze until firm.
Take from freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: skyline dip
directions: Microwave Skyline until completely defrosted.
Spread cream cheese in the bottom of a medium size baking dish until covered. Pour defrosted Skyline over cream cheese.
Sprinkle cheese and onions (optional) and serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients. Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal and mix well. Add desired nuts, raisins, chocolate chips or dried fruit. Bake until brown in a 350° oven.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with the buttermilk, coconut flavoring and coconut.
Bake in a greased and floured stem pan for 50 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: sex in a pan
directions: Combine butter, flour and chopped pecans; press in bottom of 13x9x2 inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let totally cool.
Mix powdered sugar and cream cheese; layer on crust. Spread 1 c. of cool whip on cream cheese.
Combine 1 1/2 c. of milk with each pudding and layer on top of cream cheese.
Top with 12 oz. of cool whip.
Serve chilled.

title: "newfie" corn soup
directions: In a 2-quart pot, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until soft, but not brown.
Add potatoes, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1 cup water. Cook until potatoes are soft and water is evaporated.
(Add more water, if necessary.)
Add creamed corn and evaporated milk to desired consistency.
Simmer 5 minutes over low heat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with hot Italian bread or rolls and a salad.

title: rhubarb and strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add 3/4 of mixture to fruits.
Put remaining and sugar mixture in unbaked pie shell.
Add fruit.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust.
Bake in 420° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes more.

title: haystack cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter and morsels and fold in potatoes and pecans.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: green bean side dish
directions: Steam beans with oil and dill weed to warm.
Add margarine to taste.
Serve piping hot.
This vegetable is especially good with Italian foods.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: indian corn
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces; fry until crisp, drain, reserving 2 tablespoons fat.
In reserved fat, saute green pepper and onion until tender.
Add corn, salt and pepper; heat thoroughly over medium heat.
Add cream; cook 1 minute, stirring.
Stir in bacon. Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar, add egg yolks.
Mix soda into sour cream.
Add flour and sour cream alternately to butter/sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and almond extract.

title: mexican meat casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together; pour off grease.
Mix in enchilada sauce and mushroom soup; mix well.
In casserole dish, layer Doritos, sprinkle with grated cheese. Place layer of meat mixture and layer of Doritos, and layer of meat mixture, sprinkle with cheese.
Cook in hot oven for 10 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add chicken and ham; cook and stir for 5 to 8 minutes until chicken is browned.
Stir in soup, water, beans and mustard.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice and cheese; cover.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Fluff with fork and serve.
Serves 4.

title: egg noodles
directions: If eggs are small, use a little less flour; if eggs are large use a little more flour.

title: harvest apple cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 9-inch tube pan.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Chop and peel apples.
Set them aside.
Stir together eggs and vanilla, then beat 2 minutes, until light.
Gradually add oil, beating until thick.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add dry ingredients, apples and nuts a little at a time; beat well after each addition.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Use cream cheese frosting.

title: june's jiffy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Mix batter of flour, sugar and juice.
Pour over butter.
Lay peaches over batter.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cut onion into thin slices; saute in margarine.
Add flour and pepper; cook for 10 minutes.
Add stock and Worcestershire sauce until onion is tender.

title: waffle cookie
directions: Cream margarine.
Add eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, then chocolate chips.
Heat up waffle iron.
Put 2 to 4 small teaspoons of batter,
separately, in waffle iron, making 2 to 4 cookies.
Close iron, then take out with fork.
"Great!"

title: grandmother's gingerbread
directions: Blend sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in molasses.
Combine dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until done.

title: chili cheese squares
directions: Grate cheese and mix together. Beat eggs lightly. Add canned milk to eggs and blend with cheeses. In a 9 x 13 buttered pan, cover bottom with chopped green chilies. Pour cheese mixture over chilies. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Remove, cool. Cut in 1 inch squares.

title: spaghetti(with homemade pastas of course!)
directions: In a large Dutch oven, lightly brown the meat in oil and garlic at medium-low heat.

Slowly mix in water and tomato paste. Add onions, celery and bell peppers. Simmer, covered, 3 to 5 hours until meat is very tender. Check often and add water as needed, making certain there is about a quart of thin sauce when ready to add the pasta.
Add salt, pepper and homemade pasta.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes to 1/2 hour, stirring often, until broth is absorbed.
Stir in parsley. Serves 6.

title: frozen pea salad - layered
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl in layers as listed.
Spread over this 2 cups mayonnaise mixed with 3 tablespoons sugar (seal edges as you spread).
Cover with airtight seal (I use Tupperware).

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Cook asparagus; drain.
Trim crusts from bread.
Flatten each piece with rolling pin.
Mix softened butter with cheeses.
Spread mixture on each piece of bread and top with a piece of asparagus. Roll and dip in butter.
Cut into fourths and freeze.
When ready to serve, bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 96.

title: german apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat together.
Add sliced apples and walnuts.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dan's double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat the butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs, one at a time. Beat in the brandy.
Melt the chocolate in dish over hot water. Stir the melted chocolate and sour cream into the creamed mixture. Sift together the flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir the dry ingredients gradually into the melted chocolate mixture to form a batter.
Stir in the white chocolate chips and nuts. Drop the batter by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: Mix first 8 and shape into a loaf in center of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Peel and slice potatoes, onions and carrots (sliced lengthwise).
Mix parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Place vegetables in layers around meat.
Sprinkle each layer with part of salt mixture.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more to brown meat.
Serves 4.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Combine milk, ground beef, cracker meal, onion, garlic salt, and Parmesan cheese in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Split each bun and toast lightly.
Divide meat mixture into 8 parts.
Spread one part mixture evenly over top surface of each bun.
Place on cookie sheet.
Make a well in center of meat, using the back of a spoon. Combine tomato sauce and oregano.
Spoon 2 teaspoons of mixture into each well.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons cheese over each burger.
Continue baking until cheese melts.

title: pineapple and coconut pie
directions: Pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: anisette sponges cake
directions: Mix together rum and water.
Layer one package of Sponges in a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Pour half the water and rum mixture over sponges.
Cook pudding according to directions.
While hot, pour half over sponges.

title: butter balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients; chill.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: debbie's cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water in large container; set aside.
In food processor, grind cranberries and orange.
Chop celery; mix together.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: easy french bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and yeast in large mixing bowl.
Add hot tap water and oil at one time.
Stir until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn out on floured surface and knead 10 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Put in greased bowl.
Turn cover and let rise until doubled.
Turn out.
Divide in half.
Roll each half to 12 x 15-inch.
Roll tightly from long side.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Slash top 3 to 4 times diagonally.
Let rise.

title: bean and vegetable salad
directions: Cook frozen vegetables as directed; drain and cool.
Add drained red beans.
Add diced vegetables and mix.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and mix.
Mix sugar, vinegar, flour and mustard in a small saucepan.
Cook, stirring until clear.
Cool and pour over vegetables.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Thaw sausage meat the night before.
Brown in frying pan and drain any excess fat.
Set meat aside.
Peel zucchini and slice into 1/4-inch thick rounds.
Peel and slice onions and garlic.

title: teresa's cabbage salad
directions: Saute almonds in butter; add poppy seed.
Cool.
Mix cabbage and noodles and almond mixture.
Add dressing of oil, vinegar and sugar.
Refrigerate an hour if possible.

title: benedictine spread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Add a drop of green food coloring; stir well.
Spread mixture on bread slices.
Serve as finger sandwiches.

title: baked grits
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease large baking dish with butter flavor Crisco.
Melt butter flavor Crisco in large skillet.
Add mushrooms.
Saute until mushrooms give up their liquid, about 5 minutes.
Place grits in large bowl.
Mash if they are leftovers. Add mushrooms, eggs, evaporated milk, cheese, paprika and cayenne. Stir gently to mix.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet potato - corn chowder
directions: Saute onion, garlic and sweet potato in butter or margarine until onion is translucent.
Add remaining ingredients except for corn and heavy cream.
Cook over medium heat for 45 minutes.
Add frozen corn and heavy cream.
Cook 5 more minutes over medium heat.
Adjust seasoning to taste.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given.
Mix until smooth.
(Will be thick.)
Put into Bundt pan that has been sprayed with oil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until center is done.
Let cool before cutting.
Very moist and rich.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Flour pork chops and lightly brown in oil in a heavy skillet. Remove from skillet and drain.
In a large casserole dish, stir together chicken and rice soup, water and instant rice.
Add pork chops.
Cook for 1 hour in a 375° oven.

title: mary bradshaw's bourbon hot dogs
directions: Cut hog dogs in bite size pieces.
Put on cookie sheet in 350° oven just until cuts are sealed.
Mix catsup, sugar, rosemary, oregano, basil and bourbon and bring to a boil.
Add hot dogs. Best to do day before so flavor can set in.

title: brandy's chicken
directions: Open Rice-A-Roni and sprinkle in baking dish.
Put chicken breasts on top of rice.
Mix seasoning packet in 3 cups of water in which you have dissolved the 2 chicken bouillon cubes.
Add soup to water with seasoning and mix well.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cover when bake at 350°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk.
Cook and stir.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Heat in microwave.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: diet apple pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and apple juice and bring to a boil.
Mix cinnamon, nutmeg, oleo and apples and add to juice.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Place top crust over and make several slits in top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: arabic chicken fajitas(very low-fat)
directions: Spray large wok with nonstick cooking spray; heat until very hot.
Add chicken and cook it for 4 minutes.
Remove from wok and keep it warm.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Cook broccoli cuts as per directions. Drain.
Add cream of mushroom soup, 1 can evaporated milk, 2 cans regular milk and Cheez Whiz.
Heat over medium-low flame, stirring regularly.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Beat up cheese and mix all together (can be frozen).

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in bag; place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add spaghetti sauce to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Add chicken and green peppers to bag.
Turn bag to coat chicken with sauce.
Arrange chicken in even layer. Close bag with provided tie; cut 6 half-inch slits in top of bag. Bake until tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve over hot pasta.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring the chicken stock to boil.
With a wire whisk, mix together egg whites, flour and water until smooth.
Pour a thin stream into boiling chicken stock.
Do not stir until egg mixture is cooked.
Add the soy sauce and mix well.
Ladle into consomme cups and top each serving with 1 teaspoon chopped chives or scallion tops.
Makes 3 cups.
Each 3/4 cup serving contains approximately 42 calories, 0 mg cholesterol and 167 mg sodium.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Pour batter in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash and
clean
chicken.
Salt
and pepper chicken and soak in milk overnight in refrigerator.	Flour and deep fry in Crisco until done.

title: cream cheese and pineapple spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add crushed pineapple and mix well.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: pie crust
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Pat on bottom of pan and bake until brown in 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: soupe 'a loignon(onion soup)
directions: In heavy pot, melt butter.
Add onions and cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until golden.
Sprinkle on the flour and stir for a few minutes, seasoning with salt and pepper.
Add broth and wine, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and let the soup simmer for 30 minutes, partly covered.

title: hash brown cheese bake
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake in a greased 9 x 13 pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pear pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth. Pour half of the mixture into pie shell.
Arrange pears in pie shell.
Pour remaining sour cream mixture over pears.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Bake for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings. Pan size is 9-inch.

title: fruit  dip
directions: Gradually beat orange juice into Cool Whip until the mixture is creamy, but not thin.
Add sugar to taste.
Serve with fresh or canned fruits.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough mayonnaise to moisten.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches and lemon filling together. Pour into buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Add cake mix on top, then nuts and then butter. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes until brown. (Insert knife to be sure it is done.)

title: *mary e's french dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Shake well before using.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put cracker crumbs on top.
Pour melted margarine over it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine until onion is transparent. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: skillet chicken and rice
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper in small amount of oil or butter until tender. Add chicken, salt and poultry seasoning. Continue stirring until chicken is heated.
Cook rice according to package using chicken broth instead of water. Add to sauteed ingredients and cook until dry and beginning to stick to skillet.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk. Divide into 3 graham cracker pie crusts. Top each pie with 1 can cherry pie filling and Cool Whip. Chill thoroughly.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Separate onion slices into rings.
Place in salad bowl with green pepper and tomato.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove and drain. Pour off bacon drippings.
Reserve 2 tablespoons in skillet. Stir vinegar, chili powder, salt and red pepper sauce into drippings; heat to boiling.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly.
Crumble bacon; sprinkle on top.
Serve with a slotted spoon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: delicious drumsticks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper in a bowl.
Dip chicken into butter.
Roll in flour mixture to coat. Arrange in an ungreased square pan 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake uncovered until done, about 50 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Unthaw spinach and mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Take one round loaf of baked bread and hollow out the entire center leaving only shell.
Pinch into bite size.
Pour dip in bread shell and arrange bite size pieces around outer edge.
(Dip pieces in dip mixture.)

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Add beaten egg yolks, then add milk gradually. Place over medium heat; stir constantly until mixture thickens. Remove from heat, then add vanilla. Stir well. Place into baked pie shell.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Bake at 325° until done. Makes 3 layers.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Set oven for 425°.
Combine beef and onion in baking dish. Brown in oven and drain.
Cook macaroni, then mix with spices, beef and onions.
Add 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce, tomato paste and water.
Mix in some of pepperoni.
Top with cheese, pepperoni and remaining tomato sauce.
Bake 20 minutes or until brown.

title: venison roast in gravy
directions: Soak venison roast for 4 hours in mixture of baking soda, vinegar, salt and water.
Rinse; soak in clear water 1 hour. Remove roast from water and pat dry.
Remove as much fat as possible before cooking to eliminate any gamey flavor.
Combine seasoned salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Sprinkle on both sides of roast.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.
Place onion slices on top of roast and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons flour.
Place thin slices of oleo on onion.
Wrap roast twice in heavy-duty aluminum foil. Place in roasting pan.
Add 1 quart water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 4 to 5 hours.
Add water, if necessary, to roasting pan but do not open foil.
Remove roast from pan.
Carefully open foil and measure liquid.
Combine 1 1/2 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons water to each cup of liquid.
Stir well.
Stir into roast broth. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Serve gravy with roast.

title: louisiana gumbo
directions: Brown okra in bacon drippings until okra is no longer gooey, stirring constantly (use 2 packages frozen okra and don't give up) Add onion and pepper, chopped; saute.
Add a lot of water and a little tomato sauce; let boil gently for at least 2 hours.
Add seafood, parsley, green onion tips and seasonings; cook until seafood is completely done (about 30 minutes).
Turn off fire and add file.
I use shrimp and 1 can of crabmeat; when I feel rich, I add oysters.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Combine nuts and dates. Add boiling water and stir in soda. Combine egg, vanilla and cooking oil.
Add date mixture. Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and flour. Add to date mixture and mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 1 loaf.

title: annie's old fashioned fudge
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa, milk and syrup over low heat until mixture forms a soft ball.
Stir only until sugar is thoroughly dissolved.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Let stand.
Beat until thick and creamy.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix in tomato paste, water, salsa and taco seasoning.
Add more water if sauce is too thick.
Spread small amount over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place a layer of tortillas over sauce, tearing in half to cover sides and corners.
Layer remaining as follows:
cheese, tortillas, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: greens with hot dressing
directions: Wash, drain and dry lettuce and greens.
Add chopped green onions; set aside.
Fry bacon in a large skillet until crisp; drain.
Set aside skillet with the hot bacon fat still in it. Combine the vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper in a bowl. From the reserved skillet, pour off all but about 3 tablespoons of hot fat.
Pour the vinegar mixture into the skillet.
Place skillet over the hot coals; bring mixture to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over the lettuce and spinach greens.

title: lemon freeze pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add lemonade and evaporated milk. Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
This is for 1 pie only; double ingredients for 2 pies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Add sour cream, soup and half of the shredded Cheddar.
Put mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and equal amount of stuffing on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove foil and cook for 15 minutes more.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes, macaroni, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 15 minutes on low heat.
Drain excess fat.
Add mushroom soup, little at a time. Pour ingredients into large baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top to melt as the last thing.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
